terraform plan → Compares the desired state (code) with the actual state (cloud).
terraform refresh → Updates the state file with the latest real-world values.
terraform state list → Shows resources tracked by Terraform.
Handling Drift
Identify: Run terraform plan regularly to catch mismatches.
Decide: Either accept the manual change (update Terraform code) or revert it (apply Terraform to overwrite).
Fix:
If the manual change is valid → update .tf files and run terraform apply.
If invalid → run terraform apply to restore the desired state.
